 leader in the education industry in her new role as ceo she will be responsible for the strategic vision and operational success of metrodigi she was most recently chief operating officer at the company and previously held senior positions at thompson and cengage learning prior to her tenure at metrodigi warren geddes chief financial officer geddes has more than  years of international experience in financial management for a diverse range of companies spanning finance transportation and the technology industries he will lead metrodigi in raising capital to fuel the companys aggressive growth plans and he will oversee accounting financial planning and analysis ward spangenberg chief technology officer as cto spangenberg will guide system architecture and development technology as well as expanded capabilities for metrodigi platforms including chaucer the companys critically acclaimed cloudbased authoring platform spangenberg previously served as a recognized technology leader for companies including uber zynga apple and microsoft among others daryl fox chief content officer fox has spent the past  years acquiring developing marketing and selling publishers content worldwide he will assume these same responsibilities as chief content officer for metrodigi fox previously held a variety of executive positions in the publishing industry most recently at pearson as well as educational technology company coursesmart trip gould chief product officer gould has more than a dozen years of experience leading content and product development in the field of education as a founder of mobile refactory and former professor at azusa pacific university and pasadena city college gould brings a unique blend of skills to bear in blending art technology and education into metrodigis renowned chaucer platform gould will provide strong product direction for chaucer enabling the platform to further fulfill the companys mission and vision to empower content creators in building immersive an